The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | British players lazy: Murray
                                                                                                                                                                                                     British players lazy: Murray
                      
	London: As the quintessentially English tournament of Wimbledon prepares to open, the calm and tranquil atmosphere has already been shattered by the autobiography of Britains top player.         
	World No.11 Andy Murray has delivered a withering attack on the state of British tennis on the eve of the grass court Grand Slam, which hasnt seen a home grown male player win since Fred Perry in 1936.         
	For Murray, seeded 12th at this years Wimbledon, British players are lazy, the coaches negative and the governing body unrealistic and no one is brutally honest.         
	There is something wrong with the mentality and work ethics of most of the British players, the 21-year-old Scot writes in Hitting Back published last week. (AP)                                                                                                                          
